mmetries) under such inductive transformations. The book focuses in particular on Global symmetry (invariance of adjunctions) and Internal symmetries between arrows and objects in a category (in analogy to Field Theories like Quantum Mechanics and General Relativity). The second part of the book is dedicated to more advanced applications of Internal symmetry to Computer Science: for Intuitionistic Logic, Untyped Lambda Calculus with Fixpoint Operators, Labeled Transition Systems in Process Algebras and Modal logics as well as Data Integration Theory.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCategories (Mathematics). 0aComputer sciencexMathematics. 0aInvariants. 0aSymmetry (Mathematics). 4aData Integration Theory. 4aKategorientheorie. 4aLambda-Kalkül. 4aNatürliches Schließen. 7aCOMPUTERS / Information Theory.2bisacsh  aCategory Theory.  aData Integration Theory.  aLambda Calculus.  aNatural Deduction.1 aMajkić, Zoran, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1z978311117578208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Engineering, Computer Sciences 2023 Englishz978311131912408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Engineering, Computer Sciences 2023z9783111318165oZDB-23-DEI0 cEPUBz97831110820110 cprintz978311108056740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311108167040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783111081670423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783111081670/original  a978-3-11-117578-2  DG Plus DeG Package 